@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About Movies";
}

<div class="container mt-4">
    <div class="text-center mb-5">
        <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold mb-3" style="color: #667eea;">🎬 The Magic of Cinema</h1>
        <p class="lead col-lg-10 mx-auto">
            As a team, we chose movies as our shared passion because films transcend boundaries—they allow us to relax, 
            connect with friends, and experience diverse stories and cultures, all within a couple of captivating hours.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="row g-4 mb-5">
        <div class="col-lg-8">
            <div class="about-section">
                <h4>🎭 Why Our Team Loves Movies</h4>
                <p>
                    Our diverse tastes make movie nights incredibly enriching. While some team members gravitate toward 
                    sci-fi and action-packed adventures, others prefer thought-provoking dramas or heartwarming animations. 
                    This variety creates fascinating discussions where we compare perspectives on storytelling, performances, 
                    cinematography, and soundtracks.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Movies serve as powerful conversation catalysts. After watching a film, we naturally dive into discussions 
                    about its themes, real-world connections, and whether it deserves a recommendation. These post-movie 
                    conversations often reveal insights we might have missed individually.
                </p>

                <h4>📽️ A Journey Through Cinema History</h4>
                <p>
                    Cinema's evolution began in the late 1800s when innovators experimented with capturing and displaying 
                    motion through sequential images. This technological marvel transformed into the global phenomenon we 
                    cherish today.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Silent Era (1890s–1920s)</strong><br>
                        The birth of cinema featured black-and-white films without recorded dialogue. Live orchestras and 
                        pianists provided the emotional soundtrack, creating a unique theatrical experience.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Golden Age of Hollywood (1930s–1950s)</strong><br>
                        Major studios like MGM, Warner Bros., and Paramount dominated the industry, producing iconic films 
                        with legendary stars. Narratives followed clear story arcs with memorable heroes and villains.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>New Wave & Blockbuster Era (1960s–1980s)</strong><br>
                        Visionary directors pushed creative boundaries, while groundbreaking blockbusters like <em>Star Wars</em>, 
                        <em>Jaws</em>, and <em>E.T.</em> redefined commercial cinema and established modern franchises.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Digital Revolution (1990s–Present)</strong><br>
                        CGI technology, digital cameras, and streaming platforms transformed production and distribution. 
                        Audiences now access vast film libraries instantly from anywhere in the world.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h4>🌟 The Art of Storytelling</h4>
                <p>
                    What makes cinema truly special is its ability to combine multiple art forms—writing, acting, music, 
                    and visual design—into a cohesive experience. A great film can make us laugh, cry, think deeply, or 
                    see the world from a completely new perspective. It's this transformative power that keeps us coming 
                    back to the movies time and time again.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-lg-4">
            <div class="info-box mb-4">
                <h5>💾 How MoviesHub Works</h5>
                <p>
                    We've built a comprehensive movie database using enterprise-grade SQL Server and Entity Framework Core. 
                    Our <strong>Movies</strong> section provides real-time access to our curated collection.
                </p>
                <p><strong>Each Movie Entry Includes:</strong></p>
                <ul class="list-unstyled">
                    <li>🎬 Title & Director</li>
                    <li>📅 Release Year</li>
                    <li>🎭 Genre Classification</li>
                    <li>⏱️ Runtime (minutes)</li>
                    <li>⭐ User Rating (1-10)</li>
                    <li>✨ Top Pick Status</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="feature-card">
                <h5 style="color: #667eea;">🚀 Future Vision</h5>
                <p class="small mb-2">
                    While MoviesHub currently showcases our core collection, the architecture is designed for expansion:
                </p>
                <ul class="small list-unstyled">
                    <li class="mb-1">• Personal watchlists</li>
                    <li class="mb-1">• User reviews & ratings</li>
                    <li class="mb-1">• Smart recommendations</li>
                    <li class="mb-1">• Social sharing features</li>
                    <li class="mb-1">• Advanced search filters</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center py-4">
        <a asp-controller="Movies" asp-action="Index" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg me-2">
            Browse Our Collection
        </a>
        <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="TopPicks" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-lg">
            View Top Picks
        </a>
    </div>
</div>
